description: This document defines an API that web page authors can use to detect presence of “long tasks” that monopolize the UI thread for extended periods of time and block other critical tasks from being executed - e.g. reacting to user input.
title: Long Tasks API 1

description: Navigation Error Logging defines an API to store and retrieve error data related to the previous navigations of a document.
title: Network Error Logging

description: This document defines an API that can be used to capture a series of key moments (First Paint, First Contentful Paint) during pageload which developers care about.
title: Paint Timing 1

description: This specification defines the preload relationship of the HTML Link Element (<link>).
title: Preload

description: This registry is intended to provide a central location for enumerating identified interface types of PerformanceEntry objects, which contain various data metrics for the the full lifecycle of a web application.
title: Timing Entry Names Registry
